Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Toss with @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Chop the @tomato{2} into 1cm chunks.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @oil{1%tbsp} and the @Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the tomatoes to the dressing, stir to coat, then set aside.

In a separate #bowl{}, mix together the @Aioli{1%sachet} and @Chipotle Paste{1%sachet}.

Meanwhile, place a #pot{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, fry the @Chorizo{100%g} until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once browned, stir in the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{1%sachet} and @water{100%ml}.

Bubble until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside.

Slice each @Irish Chicken Breast{320%g} lengthways into four strips.

Beat @Egg{1} in a #deep plate{}.

Add the @Breadcrumbs{1%pack} to another #plate{} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Dip the chicken first in the egg, then the breadcrumbs. Ensure it's well coated.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Place a large pan over high heat with just enough @oil{to coat} to coat the bottom.

Once hot, lay the chicken strips into the pan, lower the heat to medium-high and fry until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Turn every ~{2-3%minutes}, adjusting the heat if necessary.

Once cooked, transfer to a clean plate lined with kitchen paper.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Allow the oil to get hot so the chicken can fry properly.

Just before serving, pop the @Tortilla{8} into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide the warmed tortillas between plates, then top each with chicken strips, tomatoes, @Grated Cheese{50%g} and a spoonful of sweet chilli chorizo.

Finish with a drizzle of chipotle aioli.

Serve your fajitas with potatoes alongside.